Gnathosoma similar to female, but fixed cheliceral digit with three teeth in addition to apical tooth and movable cheliceral digit edentate; spermatodactyl simple, about as long as movable digit, directed forward at the base, slightly curved downward and tapering near apex. Dorsal shield ornamentation similar to female; without UR setae. Without presternal platelets. Sternogenital shield with five pairs of setae (
st 1 –st 5
) and three pairs of lyrifissures (
iv 1 –iv 3
); anterior margin indistinct and posterior margin slightly undulate. Endopodal shield totally fused with sternogenital shield. Without metapodal shields. Ventrianal shields wide, subtriangular, extending to area occupied by metapodal plates; not fused with exopodal or dorsal shields; bearing seven of the ten pairs of opisthogastric setae in addition to circumanal setae. Peritrematic shield fused with exopodal shield by a narrow bridge beside coxa IV and extending around its posterior margin. Leg chaetotaxy and other leg structures as in female.
